 data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2531805\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Jan 27, 2023</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104rvh1665702925360.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/rvh1665702925360.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/rvh1665702925360.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"rvh1665702925360\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">Network Settings for Improved Performance\n   </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"rvh1665702925360__network_settings_for_improved_performance_141436\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">It is possible to adjust network loads by configuring the network connections.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"rvh1665702925360__p_d46721e1_d46722e1_d46723e1\">There are several connector settings, command line switches, and assignment settings that you can use to fine-tune the network connection for optimal performance.</p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"rvh1665702925360__topic_d30417e1_d30418e1_d30419e1_d30420e1_d30421e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d997350e56\">TCP Connector Options </h2>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"rvh1665702925360__li_d23309e1_d23310e1_d23311e1\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">sb</span>, <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">rb</span>,\n                  <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">ub</span>—match the TCP/IP send, received, and message buffer sizes to\n               that of Uniface. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"bve1665702542454.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/bve1665702542454.html\">sb</a>, <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"yur1665702542590.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/yur1665702542590.html\">rb</a>, and <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"hie1665702542354.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/hie1665702542354.html\">ub</a>. </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"rvh1665702925360__li_d23312e1_d23313e1_d23314e1\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">n</span>—limit the number of network packages by turning nagling on. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"rjj1665702542678.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/rjj1665702542678.html\">n</a>.\n                       </li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"rvh1665702925360__topic_d30422e1_d30423e1_d30424e1_d30425e1_d30426e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d997350e102\">Assignment Settings </h2>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"rvh1665702925360__li_d23315e1_d23316e1_d23317e1\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$NET_TIMEOUT</span>—Specify the time that the Uniface Router should try to reestablish a connection over TCP when a connection to a server fails. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"kwv1665702694384.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/kwv1665702694384.html\" title=\"Specify the maximum length of time that one or more specified network activities can continue. Activities that can be timed out include establishing a connection to the Uniface Router, or an idle process.\">$NET_TIMEOUT</a>.\n                       </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"rvh1665702925360__li_d23318e1_d23319e1_d23320e1\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$NET_FMT</span>—Specify the format of the hit data that is returned from the server to the client. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"dps1665702719225.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/dps1665702719225.html\" title=\"Specify the compression or conversion format used to return a hitlist from the server to the client.\">$NET_FMT</a>.\n                       </li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"rvh1665702925360__topic_d30427e1_d30428e1_d30429e1_d30430e1_d30431e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d997350e137\">Command Line Switches </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"rvh1665702925360__p_d46733e1_d46734e1_d46735e1\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/maxidle</span>—Specify the maximum time the specified server is allowed to be idle (not handling any requests). For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"geh1665702717743.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/geh1665702717743.html\" title=\"Specify the maximum time a shared Uniface Server (identified by its server name (UST)), is allowed to be idle (not handling any requests).\">/maxidle</a>.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"rvh1665702925360__topic_d30432e1_d30433e1_d30434e1_d30435e1_d30436e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d997350e157\">Tuning Network Connections </h2>\n<ol class=\"ol\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"rvh1665702925360__li_d23321e1_d23322e1_d23323e1\">Edit the Uniface Router assignment file <span class=\"ph filepath\">urouter.asn</span> to specify the maximum idle time and number of reconnection attempts for the server.\n <ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"rvh1665702925360__li_d23324e1_d23325e1_d23326e1\">In the [SERVERS] section, set the maximum idle time of the shared server using <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/maxidle</span>.\n <p class=\"p\" id=\"rvh1665702925360__p_d46739e1_d46740e1_d46741e1\">It is recommended that you specify a wait period suitable for your working environment. For example, use <code class=\"ph codeph\">/maxidle=8h</code> to specify eight hours. If <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/maxidle</span> is not specified, the server continues running regardless of how long the clients are inactive.</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"rvh1665702925360__li_d23327e1_d23328e1_d23329e1\">In the [SETTINGS] section, use <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$NET_TIMEOUT</span> to specify the client connect timeout, server connect timeout, and the idle timeout.\n </li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"rvh1665702925360__li_d23330e1_d23331e1_d23332e1\">Edit the [SETTINGS] section your assignment file.\n <ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"rvh1665702925360__li_d23333e1_d23334e1_d23335e1\">Specify the format of the hit data that is returned from the server to the client using <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">NET_FMT</span>.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"rvh1665702925360__li_d23336e1_d23337e1_d23338e1\">Use the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">USYS$TCP_PARAMS</span> setting to match the TCP/IP buffer size to that of Uniface.\n <p class=\"p\" id=\"rvh1665702925360__p_d46742e1_d46743e1_d46744e1\">Uniface uses message buffers of 8192 bytes maximum for sending data packets, but some TCP/IP implementations cannot handle this size of buffer.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"rvh1665702925360__p_d46745e1_d46746e1_d46747e1\">A maximum record setting of 4096 bytes is usually appropriate, but you should reduce the maximum to the lowest maximum value supported in the network, and on both the client and server sides of the network. For example, if the client uses a maximum buffer size of 1024 bytes, and the server can support up to 4096 bytes, set <code class=\"ph codeph\">ub=1024</code> on both sides.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ol>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2531805\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2531805\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Network Settings for Improved Performance Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Jan 27, 2023 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Network Settings for Improved Performance It is possible to adjust network loads by configuring the network connections. There are several connector settings, command line switches, and assignment settings that you can use to fine-tune the network connection for optimal performance. TCP Connector Options sb , rb , ub —match the TCP/IP send, received, and message buffer sizes to that of Uniface. For more information, see sb , rb , and ub . n —limit the number of network packages by turning nagling on. For more information, see n . Assignment Settings $NET_TIMEOUT —Specify the time that the Uniface Router should try to reestablish a connection over TCP when a connection to a server fails. For more information, see $NET_TIMEOUT . $NET_FMT —Specify the format of the hit data that is returned from the server to the client. For more information, see $NET_FMT . Command Line Switches /maxidle —Specify the maximum time the specified server is allowed to be idle (not handling any requests). For more information, see /maxidle . Tuning Network Connections Edit the Uniface Router assignment file urouter.asn to specify the maximum idle time and number of reconnection attempts for the server. In the [SERVERS] section, set the maximum idle time of the shared server using /maxidle . It is recommended that you specify a wait period suitable for your working environment. For example, use /maxidle=8h to specify eight hours. If /maxidle is not specified, the server continues running regardless of how long the clients are inactive. In the [SETTINGS] section, use $NET_TIMEOUT to specify the client connect timeout, server connect timeout, and the idle timeout. Edit the [SETTINGS] section your assignment file. Specify the format of the hit data that is returned from the server to the client using NET_FMT . Use the USYS$TCP_PARAMS setting to match the TCP/IP buffer size to that of Uniface. Uniface uses message buffers of 8192 bytes maximum for sending data packets, but some TCP/IP implementations cannot handle this size of buffer. A maximum record setting of 4096 bytes is usually appropriate, but you should reduce the maximum to the lowest maximum value supported in the network, and on both the client and server sides of the network. For example, if the client uses a maximum buffer size of 1024 bytes, and the server can support up to 4096 bytes, set ub=1024 on both sides. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}